Syria to Build $948 Million Power Generation Plant, Sana Says

-- B y   L i n a   I b r a h i m
-- 
2011-06-12T09:29:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-12/syria-to-build-948-million-power-generation-plant-sana-says.html
Syria  will start construction of a
750 megawatt, 45 billion pound ($948 million) power plant within
two months in the eastern province of Deir ez-Zor, the  Syrian
Arab News Agency  said.  The Electricity Ministry also plans to rehabilitate old
power networks in the province and establish 20 transformer
stations for a cost of between 300 million pounds and 1 billion
pounds each, it said, citing Electricity Minister Imad Khamis.  There were no details about the source of funding or the
companies due to carry out the projects.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lina Ibrahim in Dubai  librahim4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
